# Help and Discovery

When adding/changing nodes or help/context menu: update node docs; help when exactly one selected; context menu = Read Guide, Copy node name, Remove.

## Node documentation

- **Add or change node**: Update `src/data/node-documentation.json`; key by `"node:<node-id>"` (e.g. `node:hexagonal-grid`). Include title, category, icon, tagline, description, inputs, outputs. Full checklist: `.cursor/rules/shaders/node-standards.mdc`.
- **Change node behavior**: Update the help entry to match current spec.

## Help and context menu

- **Help**: Enabled only when exactly one node selected; opens callout for that node type. Zero or multiple → disabled or different message.
- **Context menu** (right-click): "Read Guide" (same as Help), "Copy node name" (node type id to clipboard), "Remove" (node + connections). Dropdown; does not block canvas after close.
- Example: new node `my-node` → add `"node:my-node"` in `node-documentation.json` with description and ports.

